{"type":"step-attempt","step":"spec-review","sessionId":"1fa4a151-d43b-4790-827e-01c2002e82cf","outcome":{"verdict":"approved","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/job-power-assertion/spec-review-result-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":true,"findings":[{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"specrunner/changes/job-power-assertion/tasks.md","title":"T-04 does not assert unref() is called on the background process","rationale":"The spec requirement states the process must be unref()-ed so it does not keep the CLI event loop alive. T-04 tests env-strip, kill-idempotency, and onError plumbing but omits an explicit assertion that the fake ChildProcess's unref method was called. The KeepAlive binding provides a safety net, so a missed unref() causes at most a minor exit delay rather than a hang, but the requirement is not test-pinned."}],"observations":[{"severity":"low","file":"specrunner/changes/job-power-assertion/design.md","title":"Three independent orphan-prevention mechanisms provide strong backstop","rationale":"teardown kill(), signal-path kill(), and caffeinate -w <parentPid> are independent mechanisms. Even a crash/SIGKILL of the CLI leaves no orphan caffeinate process. This exceeds the requirement."},{"severity":"low","file":"specrunner/changes/job-power-assertion/design.md","title":"B-12 allowlist count unchanged — ratchet preserved","rationale":"spawnBackground is added to the already-allowlisted src/util/spawn.ts. No new node:child_process importer is introduced, so the shrink-only ratchet is fully preserved."}]},"followUpAttempts":1,"transientRetryAttempts":0},"startedAt":"2026-07-13T01:32:01.440Z","endedAt":"2026-07-13T01:35:32.547Z"}
